%% Category drill-down lazy-fetch flow (CategoryTreeFilter.vue)
%% Renders with: npx @mermaid-js/mermaid-cli -i sequence-category-drilldown-lazyfetch.mmd -o sequence-category-drilldown-lazyfetch.svg
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    actor User
    participant Tree as CategoryTreeFilter.vue
    participant Store as categoryStore (Pinia)
    participant Api as CategoriesApi
    participant BE as Backend (GET /products/categories)

    User->>Tree: Click expand caret on category node (parentId)
    Tree->>Store: fetchChildren(parentId)

    alt cache hit - childrenByParentId[parentId] already populated
        Store-->>Tree: return cached children[] immediately (no network call)
    else cache miss
        Store->>Store: loading = true
        Store->>Api: getCategories(parentId)
        Api->>BE: GET /products/categories?parent_id=<parentId>
        BE-->>Api: flat one-level list of children (ordered by sort_order)
        Api-->>Store: Category[]
        Store->>Store: childrenByParentId[parentId] = children
        Store->>Store: loading = false
        Store-->>Tree: children[]
    end

    Tree->>Tree: render children nodes under the expanded parent

    Note over User,BE: Selecting a radio at any level (parent or child) triggers\ncontroller.setFilter('category_id', id) -\nsee sequence-products-page-filter-pagination.mmd for that flow in full
